00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">The=
 Social-Media Stars Who Move Markets</a>=E2=80=9D and oh man is it somethin=
g:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CTraditional finance=
 is a black box,=E2=80=9D said Sarah Petite, a social-media consultant in L=
os Angeles. =E2=80=9CThis generation is looking at their parents and saying=
, =E2=80=98The way you thought about money? That isn=E2=80=99t how it works=
 anymore.=E2=80=99 =E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Instead, young=
 people want a road map to how to make big profits, and a strong independen=
t streak draws many of them to online influencers who dole out advice free,=
 rather than paying a traditional investment manager to handle their money =
for them. Many don=E2=80=99t care much about the qualifications of who=E2=
=80=99s giving the advice, experts and young investors themselves say.</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI have a rule: Don=E2=80=99t pay for s=
omething you can get free,=E2=80=9D said Rex Wu, a 33-year-old investor fro=
m Tampa Bay, Fla., who is a regular viewer of [YouTube stock-market influen=
cer and also somehow California gubernatorial candidate Kevin] Paffrath and=
 several other online finance-world personalities. He says he has invested =
a few hundred thousand dollars based on =E2=80=9Cthings I=E2=80=99ve learne=
d online from guys like Kevin.=E2=80=9D So far this year, his portfolio has=
 returned 23%; year-to-date, the S&amp;P 500 has returned 21%.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIf I were to walk into JPMorgan tomorrow, the=
y have the bias of trying to earn my business, and they might be trying to =
oversell me,=E2=80=9D Mr. Wu said. =E2=80=9CGuys online don=E2=80=99t reall=
y have anything they=E2=80=99re trying to sell me.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote=
><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Okay so between =E2=80=9Cdon=E2=80=99t pay fo=
r something you can get free=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cdon=E2=80=99t get someth=
ing free that you could pay for,=E2=80=9D I think the latter might be bette=
r advice? I mean neither is a hard-and-fast rule or anything but in the lon=
g run there is some truth to the idea that you get what you pay for? Also=
=C2=A0guys online definitely have things they=E2=80=99re trying to sell you=
?=C2=A0</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Like most internet cont=
ent, influencer videos thrive on popularity. And in the midst of a long-run=
ning bull market, what=E2=80=99s popular is success stories and hot tips on=
ly.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Many influencers report that when they =
hype an investment, they get the page views they crave. When the message is=
 bearish, however, viewers turn away, or worse, attack the messenger with v=
icious trolling. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Most [of Kevin P=
affrath=E2=80=99s] videos with positive titles garner more than 200,000 vie=
ws, he says, while videos that have negative takes on a company or an indus=
try in the title rarely get more than 60,000 views.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI have to be an astronaut and show them that the rocket s=
hip is fun, but you can=E2=80=99t look at that your whole life,=E2=80=9D Mr=
. Paffrath said.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99ll play=
 the momentum game, but let=E2=80=99s be real: True wealth comes from long-=
run interest. The trouble is, on YouTube, none of my videos about that kind=
 of thing get any views.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">Look, the thing about =E2=80=9Ctraditional finance is a black box=E2=80=
=9D is that it actually comes with a fairly complete and well-understood=C2=
=A0explanatory structure. =E2=80=9CWhy is this stock worth $X? Because the =
present value of its expected future cash flows is $X. What does that mean?=
 Well, here=E2=80=99s the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/24898515.251678/aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvRGlzY291bnR=
lZF9jYXNoX2Zsb3c/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB998e4608" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Wikipedia page</a> on discounted =
cash flow modeling, and here are six analyst reports projecting the company=
=E2=80=99s future cash flows, which are based on guidance from the company,=
 and here is a spreadsheet with all of my inputs and assumptions.=E2=80=9D =
Like it is a =E2=80=9Cblack box=E2=80=9D in the sense that, if you don=E2=
=80=99t want to bother with learning all of that stuff, you won=E2=80=99t u=
nderstand it, but that is true of most things. And it is a =E2=80=9Cblack b=
ox=E2=80=9D in the related sense that there are professionals who will worr=
y about it for you, so you don=E2=80=99t <em>have to=C2=A0</em>bother with =
learning all of that stuff. Also right yes of course that explanatory struc=
ture does not work=C2=A0<em>especially=C2=A0</em>well; stocks are regularly=
 over- or under-valued compared to their actual future cash flows, and move=
 around too much to be justified by changes in those expectations, and thos=
e professionals have a hard time beating the market. Still it is =E2=80=A6=
=C2=A0there is a way to think about it, you know?=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 16px 0;">And then meme investing in 2021 is like =E2=80=9CI have to be =
an astronaut and show them that the rocket ship is fun=E2=80=9D and yes rig=
ht in a sense all of this stuff is=C2=A0<em>simple=C2=A0</em>=E2=80=94=C2=
=A0=E2=80=9Clet=E2=80=99s all buy the same stock and then it will go up=E2=
=80=9D =E2=80=94 but =E2=80=A6=C2=A0is it not a =E2=80=9Cblack box=E2=80=9D=
? Is it not totally resistant to understanding and analysis and explanation=
 and meaning? Is it not just =E2=80=9Cthis stock is going to $10,000 becaus=
e that=E2=80=99s a very large number that is fun to say=E2=80=9D? How did y=
ou calculate that number?=C2=A0Or am I just old? Anyway I don=E2=80=99t kno=
w what to tell you but I guess a lot of people on YouTube do.</p><table cla=
