=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Kirkland &amp; Ellis, one of the top le=
gal advisers to SPACs, helped to organize other firms to issue the statemen=
t, which said the lawsuits are =E2=80=9Cwithout factual or legal basis.=E2=
=80=9D Some who signed on, like Simpson Thacher &amp; Bartlett, have compar=
atively little involvement with SPACs. They are protesting on principle, or=
ganizers said. =E2=80=9CThe market has already driven some reform,=E2=80=9D=
 said Christian Nagler of Kirkland &amp; Ellis. =E2=80=9COtherwise it shoul=
d be done by proposing rules and laws, not by lawsuits.=E2=80=9D</p></block=
quote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We talked about this <a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24898515.251678/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb=
